        "media_width": "6",
        "content_position": "topLeftSticky",
        "subheading": "",
        "title": "<p><em>Sterling Silver</em></p>",
        "description": "<p>Understated & Versatile<br/>Sterling silver is a precious metal composed of 92.5% pure silver, alloyed for strength and durability.</p><ul><li>Soft, cool-toned appearance</li><li>Lightweight and versatile<br/></li></ul><p>Silver will naturally oxidise over time, developing a darker patina, which can be polished back to its original brightness.<br/>It offers a sense of ease - effortless, minimal and quietly considered.<br/><strong>Choosing Your Metal</strong><br/>The metal you choose should feel aligned with both your aesthetic and your lifestyle.<br/>Consider:<br/></p><ul><li><strong>Tone</strong> — warm vs cool. What suits your skin tone & any coloured stones you will incorporate into your piece.</li><li><strong>Durability</strong> — how the piece will be worn daily and what your lifestyle dictates. </li><li><strong>Maintenance</strong> — Do you want something low maintenance or are you committed to upkeeping a higher demand alloy. </li><li><strong>Longevity</strong> — how the piece will age and be worn in years to come, what is the most timeless choice? </li></ul><p><br/>Often, your choice is intuitive - a connection to colour, feeling, or familiarity. Choosing the metal which best suits you is key. <br/></p>",
        "colour_style": "dark",
        "button_1_text": "",
        "button_1_link": "",
        "button_style": "underline"
      }
    },
