        "subheading": "",
        "title": "<p>A Note on Responsibility</p>",
        "description": "<p>The sourcing of precious metals is complex.<br/>While recycled materials are often considered a more sustainable option, they can present limitations in traceability. Similarly, newly mined materials require careful consideration of environmental and social impact.<br/>Our approach is to:<br/></p><ul><li>Work with<strong> trusted, accredited suppliers</strong></li><li>Source materials with c<strong>lear standards and accountability</strong></li><li>Continuously review and improve our practices</li></ul><p>We believe responsible sourcing is not defined by a single solution, but by <strong>ongoing transparency, education and evolution.</strong></p><p>Metal is more than a material - it is what carries a piece through time.</p><p>Drawn from the earth and transformed by fire and hand, it holds the stone, shapes the form, and absorbs the rhythm of daily wear.<br/> <br/>Chosen with intention, it becomes enduring: a quiet foundation for stories still unfolding.<br/><br/></p>",
        "colour_style": "dark",
        "button_1_text": "",
        "button_1_link": "",
        "button_style": "underline"
      }
    },
